        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Named Location Types"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Named locations are reusable IP address ranges or country/region groupings that CA policies reference in their Locations condition. They let you express location-based access rules symbolically (e.g., 'Corporate Network', 'Blocked Countries') without embedding specific CIDRs or country codes directly in each policy."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
